  "output": "Good picture. Analysis complete — no frontend/DB yet, so React/N+1 findings are forward-looking. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## Performance & Correctness Analysis\n\n### 1. N+1 Queries — Not applicable yet\nNo DB layer exists. Flag for when FastAPI routes are built: avoid loading `GameState` per-player in a loop. Load once, filter in Python.\n\n---\n\n### 2. React re-renders — Not applicable yet\nNo frontend built. SvelteKit has reactivity pitfalls instead — flag when frontend starts.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Memory Accumulation (real bug)\n\n**`incoming_orders` grows forever and is never read.**\n\n`place_orders` appends to it every round (`order_processor.py:72`), but `fulfill_orders` reads from `orders_this_round` directly (`order_processor.py:31`). After 26 rounds, each player has 26 dead entries. The list is pure waste.\n\n```python\n# place_orders — appends every round, never consumed:\nupstream_ps.incoming_orders.append(order_qty)   # line 72\n\n# fulfill_orders — reads orders_this_round, NOT incoming_orders:\ndemand_by_role[role] = state.orders_this_round.get(downstream, 0)  # line 31\n```\n\nFix: either remove `incoming_orders` from `PlayerState` entirely (dead field), or make `fulfill_orders` consume it. Given the current design uses `orders_this_round` as the authoritative source, just drop the field:\n\n```python\n# In place_orders, remove this:\n- upstream_ps.incoming_orders.append(order_qty)\n\n# In PlayerState model, remove:\n- incoming_orders: list[int] = Field(default_factory=list)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Redundant Computation\n\n**`advance_shipments` iterates `incoming_shipments` twice** (`order_processor.py:7-13`):\n\n```python\n# Two passes today:\narrived = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1)\nps.incoming_shipments = [\n    IncomingShipment(..., arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1)\n    for s in ps.incoming_shipments\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds > 1\n]\n```\n\nSingle-pass fix:\n```python\narrived = 0\nremaining = []\nfor s in ps.incoming_shipments:\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1:\n        arrived += s.quantity\n    else:\n        remaining.append(IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1))\nps.inventory += arrived\nps.incoming_shipments = remaining\n```\n\nAlso: `IncomingShipment` objects are reconstructed wholesale each round just to decrement a counter. Consider mutating in-place (remove Pydantic's frozen constraint if set) or using a plain dataclass/tuple.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Correctness Bug Disguised as Redundancy\n\n**`PlayerState.round_cost()` uses wrong constants** (`game.py:41-42`):\n\n```python\ndef round_cost(self) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT + self.backlog * BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT\n```\n\nUses module-level defaults (`HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT = 0.5`, `BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT = 1.0`), not `GameConfig` values. If a variant sets custom costs, `round_cost()` lies. `accrue_costs()` in `order_processor.py:86-91` correctly uses `state.config`. This method either needs access to config or should be deleted — callers should use `accrue_costs` results.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Caching Opportunity\n\n**`GameState.is_round_complete()`** (`game.py:56-57`) rebuilds a set every call:\n```python\ndef is_round_complete(self) -> bool:\n    active_roles = {role for role, ps in self.players.items() if not ps.is_ai}\n    return active_roles.issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\n`active_roles` never changes during a game. Compute once at game start and cache:\n```python\n# In create_game():\nstate._human_roles = frozenset(r for r, ps in players.items() if not ps.is_ai)\n\n# In is_round_complete():\nreturn self._human_roles.issubset(self.orders_this_round.keys())\n```\n\n(Or add `human_roles: frozenset[PlayerRole]` as a proper Pydantic field.)\n\n---\n\n### Priority\n\n| Issue | Severity | File |\n|-------|----------|------|\n| `incoming_orders` never consumed | Medium — dead data growing each round | `game.py:36`, `order_processor.py:72` |\n| `round_cost()` wrong constants | High — returns incorrect values with custom config | `game.py:41` |\n| Double iteration in `advance_shipments` | Low — bounded by `shipping_delay`, ~4 items | `order_processor.py:7-13` |\n| `is_round_complete()` set rebuild | Low — 4 players, negligible | `game.py:56` |\n\nThe `round_cost()` correctness bug is the most important fix before Sprint 2 adds variant-specific costs.\n",
